    "country": "USA",
    "bio": "Carlos Rivera is an Associate Professor in the Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering at MIT, jointly appointed in the Institute for Data, Systems, and Society. His research develops hybrid discrete-choice models that incorporate neural-network components for utility specification, applied to travel-demand and technology-adoption settings across Latin America.\n\nHe holds a PhD from UC Berkeley (2016) and a BS from the Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México. Before MIT he led the analytics group at the Inter-American Development Bank's Transport Division, where he developed forecasting models for EV diffusion across six Latin American countries — work that forms the basis of his ISA 2026 presentation.\n\nHis projects have been funded by NSF, the Volpe Center, and the Hewlett Foundation. Outside of research he co-chairs MIT's annual Latinx in Transportation symposium and mentors first-generation undergraduates through the MIT Summer Research Program.",
