    "bio": "Mei Chen is an Associate Professor of Economics at Tsinghua University's School of Economics and Management. Her work bridges experimental economics and reinforcement-learning theory, asking how artificial agents and human subjects update risk preferences under shifting reward environments.\n\nShe earned her PhD from Stanford in 2018 and was a visiting researcher at the Max Planck Institute for Human Development before joining Tsinghua. Her recent paper on RL agents and risk preference, presented at ISA 2026, has been featured in Nature Human Behaviour and was awarded the SHEN Honghai Prize for Young Economists in 2025.\n\nShe co-directs the Tsinghua Behavioral Lab and serves on the editorial board of Experimental Economics.",
